text:
[ l dans ville ] • mathilde castres, 38 ans est la fondatrice de la @sinequanonrun  prévue le 13 octobre au parc de la villette. ouverte à toutes et tous, son intention est de montrer, un an après #metoo, que la société est prête à évoluer vers plus d’égalité et de respect. au bord du canal de l’ourcq, mathilde revient sur son parcours et ses espoirs. son rapport à la ville et la société. un tout qui se cristalliserait en ces lieux.
•
« j’aime cet endroit pour l’eau. cette symbolique de la circulation, de l’échange, des rencontres. mais c’est aussi un lieu où, le soir en tant que femme, je peux avoir peur de m’y aventurer. alors que faire ? laisser ce lieu drainé par la peur ? non, on doit l’investir tous ensemble pour qu’il puisse continuer à vivre.  et la sin qua non run va dans ce sens !

l’idée de cette course m’est venue après avoir subi le harcèlement de mon employeur lorsque je travaillais à montréal. en en parlant autour de moi, je me suis rendue compte que ça faisant 25 ans que cet homme agissait ainsi. la plupart des victimes n’avaient jamais osé parler, finissant par considérer que c’était la norme. alors qu’on me conseillait de partir et oublier, je me suis dit que si je ne faisais rien, cet homme continuerait à agir. tout d’un coup, j’ai pris conscience d’un problème et son ampleur. il fallait agir. on ne peut pas accepter ça et vivre avec des traumatismes sans jamais rien dire. on ne peut pas envisager une société basée sur des valeurs aussi peu respectueuses. 
après avoir porté plainte, j’ai donc voulu transposer cette énergie pour moi et les autres victimes, mais aussi les hommes en créant cette course. cette idée de partir d’un point a : la société actuelle, pour arriver à un point b : la société où l’on se respecte entre humains. quel que soit le genre, les origines, les orientations sexuelles. partager nos foulées pour aller là où l’on souhaite aller.

si je ne me considérais pas comme féministe – sans doute par peur du mot - aujourd’hui,  je l’assume. celui du féminisme humanisme qui œuvre pour une mixité ! un dialogue entre toutes et tous ! »
•
#lesambitieuses #borntobeambitious #borntobeavoice #femmes #ville #société #paris

l’idée de cette course m’est venue après avoir subi le harcèlement de mon employeur lorsque je travaillais à montréal. en en parlant autour de moi, je me suis rendue compte que ça faisant 25 ans que cet homme agissait ainsi. la plupart des victimes n’avaient jamais osé parler, finissant par considérer que c’était la norme. alors qu’on me conseillait de partir et oublier, je me suis dit que si je ne faisais rien, cet homme continuerait à agir. tout d’un coup, j’ai pris conscience d’un problème et son ampleur. il fallait agir. on ne peut pas accepter ça et vivre avec des traumatismes sans jamais rien dire. on ne peut pas envisager une société basée sur des valeurs aussi peu respectueuses. 
après avoir porté plainte, j’ai donc voulu transposer cette énergie pour moi et les autres victimes, mais aussi les hommes en créant cette course. cette idée de partir d’un point a : la société actuelle, pour arriver à un point b : la société où l’on se respecte entre humains. quel que soit le genre, les origines, les orientations sexuelles. partager nos foulées pour aller là où l’on souhaite aller.

si je ne me considérais pas comme féministe – sans doute par peur du mot - aujourd’hui,  je l’assume. celui du féminisme humanisme qui œuvre pour une mixité ! un dialogue entre toutes et tous ! »
•

text:
it’s #worldmentalhealthweek and sharing the work of movers championing mental health and healing continues.
💫

@_curvyballerina_ is a classically trained ballerina, an art model, and a survivor of sexual assault. she founded @balletafterdark, a concierge dance-fitness studio, to provide ballet-based self-care programs tailored towards women who have been through sexual and/or domestic violence, and disenfranchised women facing trauma at any level in their lives. the mission of the workshops is to provide a safe environment and help others heal through dance and self-care strategies.
.

we were lucky to speak with this changemaker several months ago and learn more about her journey. the story up soon on the new free body project website at freebodyproject.org.
.

in @_curvyballerina_ ‘s words: 👑✨🌟... heal how you feel...🌟✨👑 we're healing at ballet after dark..visit and subscribe at balletafterdark.com.
. .

.

text:
shocking revelations were made on social media on thursday when filmmaker subhash ghai was accused of rape, with an anonymous woman alleging that he spiked her drink and then sexually assaulted her. the producer-director has “strictly and firmly” denied this allegation. 
also, journalist karishma upadhyay shared her account of khan allegedly indulging in dirty talks when she had gone to his sister’s house to interview him. she alleged that he even forcibly kissed her. later , he allegedly body-shamed her when they were working on an mtv project. 
src- the indian express

text:
#metoo is taking the world by storm and the kind of people who are being revealed to be monsters, silent perpetrators, spectators is crazy out there. 
consent is a very important word. even in relationships, having your partner respect your wish goes a long way in determining how healthy your relationship will be. 
why this post? 
because i want to tell people out there to stand up against abuse. why am i talking about it now? because as a child when you don't know any better, there are men/women lurking out there who will rob you of your innocence and silence you by making you guilty about the act. what was the 6 or 9 year-old kid's fault? it can be a boy or a girl kid. the abuser can be a man or a woman.

and then you see them, still around you as you grow up and the anger you feel when those memories you hid in the corners of your mind comes seeping in from those crevices. 
i've a strong desire to never have kids. mainly because i don't want them to see this cruel bad world. where monsters hide behind friendly faces, in that neighborhood bhaiya who offers to buy you chocolate or the uncle who visits home too often. 
i've never spoken about this before because it is a very sensitive topic and i never felt the need to speak about it. but my heart is gripped by this fear when i see kids in common spaces, in creches, in school buses, in parks. they need to be taught to protect themselves. 
teach them to tell what is wrong. teach them to understand it wasn't their fault. it was them. their sick twisted minds.  i can't let them shame me anymore. .
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#metoo #protectyourchildren #timeforachange #childsafety #besafe #keepthemsafe #courage #notafraid #dontbeafraidanymore #teachyourkidstobesafe

text:
mental health 
alot of people inspired me to say something. so here it goes. anxiety is never fun. its not always that obvious and not really easy to spot but man is it real and when it gets out of control, it can be scary for others and myself. ive had my share of attacks that have scared my loved ones. it makes me feel like something is extremely wrong with me. but as i have come to learn, that is not the case. there are so many people that have very similar feelings. its always good to know that others feel what i feel. and its also good to know i have family and friends that love me despite the anxiety. im so grateful to not feel alone.

thank you for the photo edit: mark arellano

text: just finished a fabulous session of #speedmentoring for @womenoftheworldaustralia whilst it was phenomenal to spend such quality time with four young women (and zip around the @wheelofbrisbane a couple of hundred times!), i found it disheartening to listen to the challenges that they, as year 10 students, were experiencing: #genderroles and #stereotypes perpetrated by teachers, the phrase #boyswillbeboys given as excuses to the bad behaviour of schoolmates, #sexualharassment in the schoolyard, the empowering slogans of #grlpwr and #youcandoanything being said on assembly but not followed up by real, tangible action. it disheartens me that, despite the progress being made on #genderinequality globally, despite the prolific #metoo and #timesup movements, despite how much work has gone into #feminism, we still have so, so far to go. until every woman is free from inequality, until ever girl is free from inequality, then none of us are free from this gendered inequality. #internationaldayofthegirl

text: two #inktober days — day 11 #cruel and day 9 #precious . the “cruel” one is a reimagining of the popular subject matter of the suicide of lucretia, the roman noblewoman who was a victim of rape by a roman prince. when her pleas for justice are ignored in front of the magistrate, she tears open her dress to reveal a dagger and pierces her heart on the spot. with this reference, i wanted to communicate the inherent cruelty of the way victims of sexual assault are forced to relive their trauma (symbolized by the dagger) when they speak about their experiences, especially to those in power. the blood coming out of her wound reads “self-sacrifice.” the gag (which is not a part of normal lucretia paintings) is meant to signify how the testimony of victims is often dismissed as contrived and false out of a well-intentioned desire protect the men of the community. despite this bleak reality, telling your story can have far-reaching effects even when the justice system fails you. in the original story, outrage over lucretia’s rape and suicide ultimately resulted in overthrow of the monarchy and establishment of the roman republic. speaking out is vital and costly work. thank you to all who are brave enough to do it. #metoo #rapeoflucretia #lucretia #arthistory

text:
zijn wij wel gelijk?
.
door het project van @stvluchteling (waarvoor deze illustratie is gemaakt) ben ik gaan nadenken hoe goed wij het hier wel niet hebben. niet alleen in kansen, maar ook in gelijkwaardigheid. dit is uiteraard een langzaam proces geweest, maar wij (en dan bedoel ik vrouwen in het algemeen) mogen zeker niet klagen over de kansen die we nu hebben. dat we er nog niet helemaal zijn weten we allemaal. zo is de medische wereld voornamelijk ingesteld op het mannelijk lichaam & worden vrouwen nog steeds gediscrimineerd op de arbeidsmarkt (ja ook ik heb dit meegemaakt. zo kreeg ik ooit eens de vraag tijdens een sollicitatie wanneer ik aan kinderen wilde beginnen. je begrijpt mijn mond viel open. dat is een vraag die uiteraard niet gesteld mag worden. ik was dan wel weer zo brutaal om te antwoorden dat ik over een week was uitgerekend & 15 kinderen wilde van 8 verschillende mannen. dat ik het niet werd voor die functie is mij nog steeds een raadsel). heb jij wel eens wat meegemaakt dat je dacht 'hier klopt iets niet'? daar ben ik wel benieuwd naar.
.
ps. een heel leuk & leerzaam account om te volgen is @zeikschrift . hoe madeleijn zich weet te verwoorden over #metoo en andere zaken is goud waard!
.
.
.
.

door het project van  (waarvoor deze illustratie is gemaakt) ben ik gaan nadenken hoe goed wij het hier wel niet hebben. niet alleen in kansen, maar ook in gelijkwaardigheid. dit is uiteraard een langzaam proces geweest, maar wij (en dan bedoel ik vrouwen in het algemeen) mogen zeker niet klagen over de kansen die we nu hebben. dat we er nog niet helemaal zijn weten we allemaal. zo is de medische wereld voornamelijk ingesteld op het mannelijk lichaam & worden vrouwen nog steeds gediscrimineerd op de arbeidsmarkt (ja ook ik heb dit meegemaakt. zo kreeg ik ooit eens de vraag tijdens een sollicitatie wanneer ik aan kinderen wilde beginnen. je begrijpt mijn mond viel open. dat is een vraag die uiteraard niet gesteld mag worden. ik was dan wel weer zo brutaal om te antwoorden dat ik over een week was uitgerekend & 15 kinderen wilde van 8 verschillende mannen. dat ik het niet werd voor die functie is mij nog steeds een raadsel). heb jij wel eens wat meegemaakt dat je dacht 'hier klopt iets niet'? daar ben ik wel benieuwd naar.
.
ps. een heel leuk & leerzaam account om te volgen is  . hoe madeleijn zich weet te verwoorden over  en andere zaken is goud waard!
.
.
.
.

text:
all i know is metoo

it was 12 in the noon,

i was walking,

wearing a plain t shirt and a jeans.

there were men on the street,

some passed by me,

others chose to stop and take a look,

like i was a mannequin in a showroom,

but did i tell you, i was a human?

a human who could hear,

when they called me by names,

a human who could see,

when they made me feel ashamed.

but i chose to ignore,

because that’s what i was taught.

hear and ignore,

until your last breath.

it’s 12 in the night,

i lie under a street light,

wearing nothing but a sheet,

there is no one in the sight.

no one passes by,

no one to share my plight.

i sit here like a stone,

but did i tell you, i am a human?

a human who felt everything,

a human who had screamed,

when unknown hands ran over me,

when they destroyed me from within.

and now i couldn’t ignore,

because i could see se clear,

what i felt like,

to be treated like her,

i sit here broken 
quietly, in the couch,

behind a 5 inch screen,

my thoughts racing about.

now all i know is 
me too.

______________________

credits: @vanshika_dance

text:
two separate instances in this fit: 
1.) i was at a local bar and felt someone tap my ass, i turned around and watched as the man who did it proceeded to walk on stage and sing bc he was the live entertainment! later a short, bald man leaned on me and stared, eyes wide, waiting for me to acknowledge him. i ignored his aang-lookin ass despite that every time i moved, he followed and pressed his stupid sweaty body against my legs while i sat on a half wall, drunk and tired. 
2.) i went through the west village all day, and more than 3 men whistled and followed me while i was with my family. later at night i passed a stoop and a man stopped his conversation with another man to say “nice babe, where you goin?” he whistled and i kept walking. and when i walked back home i did so on the other side of the street to avoid him. my sister didn’t understand why i made her cross with me until i explained it and i’m happy she doesn’t have to think about these things like i do. #metoo

text: the me too campaign is running at its peak. the dirty linen is out and the stench is everywhere. i am a victim and that too as a 11 year old child, not to mention a few instances when i was older. fortunately, i dealt with it. but as this campaign grows and as much as i relate to it, it’s unfortunate that a  lopsided view arises out of it. yes, women are more the victims but it would be the right time to point out that men too have gone through this trauma. and even though the campaign has emerged as a symbol towards women’s rights, i would like to do my bit and stand by all those men who have endured sexual abuse. why do i care to add this dimension ? because recently i found out that men ( friends of friends: yes people who i don’t know) had been victims of sexual abuse. it is not my place to say what happened and how it all conspired, because  it is their secret to share. but them sharing this secret is clouded with fear, a greater one, because there is no law or society to protect them: because no one would believe them. i cannot help but remember ayn rand when she said,” the smallest minority is the individual”. if we could make people realise this issue to be an individual one, we as women who have been given a voice through this #metoo campaign would come out as bigger winners. #mentoo as much as #metoo

text: we are in a place of multiple feminisms, where one’s idea of feminism intersects with another. there are radical feminists, feminists and anti-feminists and many such groups that i may not be aware of. judging from the generations gone by, this is expected, ofcourse, because the idea of feminism started when one woman noticed how her husband sat on the couch reading a newspaper with his empty cup of tea lying on the table, while she “worked” as part of her role as a wife. we’ve come a long way since then, with women being the breadwinners of the family, men becoming house-husbands, women and men reaching c-suite positions, both trying to bring about better change in the world. the #metoo movement has had a huge impact in the world today, especially india. this is where social media brings about positive change in the world. it’s deeply saddening to know how men view/viewed women. but there is a huge number of men who have experienced similar, if not worse, situations. let’s stand up for humanity, for human beings, for equality. this is real feminism.

text:
the metoo and timesup movement is getting bigger with every minute and many shocking allegations and incidents are brought to the light. we saw actors samantha, varalaxmi, aditi rao hydari, siddharth, amyra dastur, singer shaktisree gopalan, and few others, extending their support to the movement and to chinmayi's bold steps in this issue. 
the latest celebrity to join and support this movement is actress kajal aggarwal who took to her twitter space to post her statement. she tweeted, "it takes tremendous courage to face your demons and speak up. i support all the women who're standing up for themselves & for their integrity. cannot fathom the horror any sort of unwanted advances must’ve left on the minds&souls of all these brave women who’ve spoken up. #metoo

we, women need to stand up for each other, defend and stay true in testing times. for those who feel women do this as a publicity propaganda, pls do not trivialize and sling mud as that doesn’t speak very highly of your thought process and intentions. #metoo #metooindia #timesup"

text:
it just so happened that on world mental health day i saw my therapist. i’ve been seeing her in waves for many years now and it is the bravest thing i have ever done. anyone who takes a moment to look at their deepest pain is a hero. it takes so much courage to heal the heart and everyone who is on that path to healing is brave, strong and is my hero. 
keep on the path even when it’s hard because it is worth it. you will heal. it will happen and it may take a long time but it happens in the smallest of steps and in the leaps you make. i believe in love and i believe in healing. 
this week i am full of gratitude for all the love and help i’ve had along the way. we say that it takes a village to raise a child but i think it takes a village to support a human being, from birth until death. i am so thankful for the village of people who support me. we need each other. and look at all this sunshine! it’s beautiful!! today my heart is at peace 💜 
thanks for your time and attention 🙏🏻💜
.
.
.

text:
this was me, on monday, on the way to the police. (the people, not the band.)
sunday morning, after work - so around seven am - i got to my front door where there was a note i wanted to photograph. as i did that, i noticed someone behind me, thinking one of my neighbours needed to get past. i turned around, but there was a man. weirded out, i turned back and at the same time realised that i'd seen him a year before with @geraldinediercks when he was doing what i noticed he was doing this time: he was masturbating. while a valid past-time in general and harmless that first time as we were passing him by, this time he'd actively come to me (no pun intended) and didn't even budge when i turned around again. i went inside and quickly upstairs.
i didn't think it would faze me much. people do that all the time, so what if he was right behind me? but if a year ago he just stood there, this time he followed me - what's next time? will he be even more forward with the next person or when i get off a similar shift? and now i look into doorways more. @yokohama_zarnecki gave me a pocket alarm and i accepted it. i try to see as soon as i turn the corner whether someone's in front of my door. and when my shadow overtakes me between street lamps, i get uneasy. because of that guy. he didn't physically harm me, at least this time. but how dare he change my mindset? how dare he make me feel unsafe or dependant? in an age of #metoo, how dare someone impose on someone else like this and how dare i still be surprised?
i don't know. i'm not even really sure what the point of this post is. i guess awareness. some people (mostly, of course, straight white males 🖤) don't understand just how common these things are. we encounter situations like these all the time, we're just so used to them, we don't make a big deal anymore. well, that's over. i'll be loud about every guy who gives me bad sauna memories, every idiot who thinks i owe him sex and every beyond-inappropriate issue. because it's not fair to ask us to deal with it. that's not our job.

well, those my thoughts on my first time going to the police - who'd have thought it'd be for something like this? (everyone.)
#webelieveyou

text:
guilty until proven innocent is not justice. the victim is not always the accuser.
•

text:
for all the women coming out with their stories - more power to you. women have been silent for too long. but there are so many women still out there whose voices are stifled, who are unable to speak up. they may come from difficult economic conditions, they may be dependent and have a family to feed. these women are brave, but still suffering. we support you. we feel your pain. we want to cry with you.

to the men helping this movement - your support is welcome and very much needed. we cannot do this alone. we must come together and build a country of unity and mutual respect. we must fight for the country that we want to leave for our daughters - and sons.

to the men who think this is all drama - please get educated. ask your female friends, colleagues and family members what they feel, what they’ve experienced. perhaps you’ve never taken the time to really listen and understand?

to the women who don’t support this movement, who think that ‘men will be men’, who discourage other women from coming forward because they don’t want drama and backlash, because they don’t want to ‘taint’ the man’s reputation, who feel that women are supposed to suffer silently - because of you, things have not changed for so long.

when women support women, amazing things happen. 
#metooindia

#metoo #metooindia #metoomovement #metoostories #metoostory #timesup #nomoresilence #womenrise #timeforchange #strongertogether #womenrights #womenempowerment
#safetyforwomen #indianwomen #strongindianwomen #equalrights #workplacesexualharassment #supportwomen #notallmen #safeindia #saveourdaughters #indiaforchange

text:
fight for them - they are our future
listen to them - they have a voice
empower them - make them strong 
teach them - they will teach others
protect them - and the world will change

today, i reflect on @trevornoah 's excerpt on @thedailyshow and the inciteful commentary on trump weaponizing victimhood. i listened to @lynzylab 's song. i contemplate @flotus melania trump's statement regarding evidence and @realdonaldtrump 's fears of a scary world for boys. i weep because 1 in 3 women will be assaulted in her lifetime. i was - i don't know a woman who hasn't been. but i do not seek your sympathy, rather your action. find your voice. empower yourself. tell your story. they question why we wait, why we are silent - don't be silent. speak out. and to all the men out there who are "scared": if you have never assaulted a woman, you have nothing to fear. surround yourself with fierce woman because we not only protect ourselves, but you too, your wives, your mothers, your daughters. you have everything to gain and nothing to lose. we on the other hand have already lost a piece of our soul and stand to lose so much more. that stops now... #aperio #metoo #sexualassault #bekind #neveragain #believewomen #dayofthegirl #christineblaseyford #donaldtrump #weaponization #victim #victimhood #assault #nomeansno #believeher #trevornoah #donaldtrump #timesup #melaniatrump #lynzylabstewart #lynzylab #empowerment #vote #november6

text:
i am unfortunately just 1 out of 100,000,00 women around the world, that has faced sexual assault in their life time. although it happened to me almost 2 years ago, i suppressed all my thoughts regarding my sexual assault & never really accepted that i was a victim, like many other women, until a few weeks ago. although this happened to me a while ago, it has forever changed me as a person, but i know that it won’t define me & i will come out stronger on the other side. so i decided to write a poem as a coping mechanism, to deal with all my emotions lately. to whomever reads this, i hope you enjoy & that if you have also dealt with sexual assault, that you realize, it is never your fault. please talk to someone, a friend, a trusted adult, someone & remember you’re never alone in this. 💗
enjoy reading.🌻
full poem below: 
#metoo

this hashtag that’s sparked a national debate,
you call it a mere attention seeking move,
diminishing the point that many of us are trying to prove.
so here’s another attempt to shed light on this issue,
yes, unfortunately #metoo.

at just eighteen years old, your touch it burned my soul.
it’s a distant past my dear, you might say,
but your filthy smirk will forever stay.
not showers, nor time will undo
that ever so poisonous memory of you.

i loathe you, although i am no longer in your embrace.
you, and the dozen bystanders in that public place.
who pretended to not notice your lustful embrace.
but in the end you walked away,
and they said it was my fault anyways.

i asked for it, remember?
my clothes & my inches of exposed skin, begged for your unwanted touch.
i asked for it, remember? or am i asking of you too much? just like when i pleaded for you to stop, but you insisted that it just be, “one quick touch”. believing them i tried to change the way i look,
the way i dress, meticulously abiding every instruction.
so i don’t accidentally tempt your unnerving perversion.
while all you wear is that lecherous smile, that years later, still sends shivers down my spine.

yet, you still believe you did nothing wrong.
you blurred my perception of lust and appreciation,
made me cringe at the touch of true passion.
(continued below 👇🏼👇🏼👇🏼)

text: it’s been a year since the #metoo movement. it was very painful and still is but i am grateful for it. last october was one of the worst times of my entire life. i’m still struggling. i thought for the longest time many of the things i allowed to happen to me were normal. my focus and energy were wasted for a long time on “seeking revenge” on men who want to objectify women and think it’s funny. destroying fuckboys basically. as funny as it was at times i wasted my energy and my body on these people. if you’re not on my level i just don’t fuck with you. if someone mistreated you, speak out. always. but to them, personally. if they assault you then cut them off. protect yourself and your heart, mind and body. listen to and support others. be unapologetic about who you are and never change yourself for a partner or let them control you. be sure to open communication with this person, and if they cease communication you were never the problem. happy october.

listen up: @gretajanepaperco is on a mission to do something beautiful for a woman in need. let’s do this 🖤🖤🖤
repost: in 1991, anita hill came forward with her assault allegations against justice clarence thomas. her accusations were met with the same dismissive treatment as was recently incurred by dr. christine blasey ford. after the hearings, anita hill began receiving handwritten letters of support and gratitude for having stood up and told her story. 
in an article for time magazine that came out in 2011, anita hill explained how those letters comforted her and motivated her to keep fighting the good fight - and not just against sexual harassment but against gender, racial, class and ethnic inequality.

text:
forever destined to be surrounded by amazing girls and women ❤️ .
.
.
when i was a little girl someone bought me pyjamas that said “anything boys can do girls can do better..” with a picture of a little girl wearing a baseball hat holding a bat. i wore those pyjamas all the time and very much believed those words to be true. but then i grew up and realized that was not how the world viewed girls/ women. .
.
.
my daughters are still to young to understand the issues in the world concerning women’s rights; the #metoo and #timesup movements.
.
.
.
my hope for them and all future women is that these will be issues of the past.  that they will be free to speak their mind and stand up for themselves without fear of being judged or labeled as “bitchy” or “opinionated”. i want them to feel valued and understood. to know that it’s ok to cry when you’ve had enough (that doesn’t make you a weak girl). but most of all i want them to have equal opportunities in which ever direction they choose to go. .

we’ve come a long way....but we can do better! .
#internationaldayofthegirl #thefutureisfemale #momofgirls #auntofnieces #mycrew #raisestrongdaughters

to all my dear dames out there
.
fight your battles today,
do not be pushed,
do not be abused,
do not be weak,
speak.
do not wait for someone
to take the stand for you.
be the light of the night,
be the knight of your life.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
#himtoo
i was really disappointed when i found out what this hashtag was for. i really could not be any more disappointed than to find out that so many people have completely missed the point of the issue. so for any of the people who do not bother to educate themselves, here are some stats for you:
• every 98 seconds someone is sexually assaulted.
• out of 1,000 rapes, only 310 are reported - this means that about 2/3 go unreported
• only 2-10% of rape accusations are false - this is no higher than false accusations for other major crimes.
• 1 out of 6 women is a victim of an attempted or completed rape.
• about 3% of men are victims

so while most people believe - as long as you do the right thing and follow the law, you have nothing to worry about- when it comes to other crimes, why is this any different? it's not. 
instead of being worried about a false accusation, that has a slim chance of happening in the big picture, you should be worried about the chance of being sexually assaulted yourself or someone you care for being sexually assaulted. the scale of the problem of sexual assault is so much larger than the problem of false accusations.
stop trying to invalidate victims who finally have the courage to speak up.

so back to the stats, out of 310 reported rape cases, only 6 rapists will be incarcerated. rape is extremely difficult to prove for many reasons. so if men who do rape do not receive punishment, why would you be so worried that your life will be ruined and you will receive punishment for something you did not do? when we think about how rare false accusations are, we should feel ashamed at the way victims who have the courage to speak up not only for themselves but also for others are treated. i'm not saying a fair trail should be out of the picture, i'm saying that victims should be shown respect once they speak up, during a case, and after the case, even if they did not win.
 #himtoo should be no different than #metoo. let's all focus on the real issue instead of trying to sweep it under the rug and belittle it by making such a small issue much bigger than the real, widespread issue.

text:
"accept the things you cannot change. change the things you cannot except." as a company, we do not accept #childabuse #poverty #domesticviolence #childendangerment and we not only want to see change, but are about being the change. with so many movements out there, division, politics, first world problems....it's easy to find things to gripe about. but let's put our money where our mouth is. let's stand up for the orphan, the widow, the weak.
we had the honor of creating this invitation for @coyotehillkids for their #bootsnbids fundraiser tonight. but the buck doesn't stop there, i'm personally asking you to forgo your luxury coffee tomorrow and donate $5 to something, someone, some child that will have eternal value. link is in the comments to donate today. 
it's never too late to actually do something!
also big thanks to our dear friend for watching our little one at a last minute notice. @mamafisher7

text:
feminism. what's it mean to you? for me, it's that gender is a construction and we should all construct our own for ourselves and support others in theirs without judgement and with safety.

my feminism feels on fire today. i'm pissed and scared and all the things... witnessing our culture go through the kavanaugh hearings has been more painful physically, emotionally, intellectually, and spiritually than ever expected.

when liz phair's (@lizphairofficial) "exile in guyville" came out in 1993, i was 14 and it made all the sense in the world to me.  her words (completely cisgender, i know) included being pissed, calling bullshit, and  sex... her sex and how she liked it.

sex was so confusing to me. i liked boys a lot and i had been sexually abused by men. i wanted to be liked by boys and i didn't wanna wear pink, listen to bubble gum pop, or have any interest in being a mom. i was scared of sex and the power i felt i'd be giving to men if i let them touch me. would i just be asking to be abused again? if you've been abused, can you even like sex? am i a slut?

i'm not saying phair's album answered all these questions but she was singing about her questions; questions that too many people avoid saying out loud. i needed to know i wasn't the only girl questioning, scared, pissed and excited by sex and all that comes with our gendered experiences.

so a couple weeks ago, i saw phair for the first time (after decades of listening to that album on a regular basis through today) and i sang with her loud and proud. i so wish that over those decades any of those questions had gotten easier. and, today, as our gendered world lies in grossness spewed by our elected "leaders" and so many others.... i'm more scared and pissed of our gendered world than i was in 1993.

text:
thank you to @prochoiceoregon for kismet-ingly hosting the 2018 naral gala last night. the past couple weeks have been excruciating and last night a room full of empathetic pro-women, pro-choice progressive rock stars was the best place to be. thank you, thank you, thank you!

to the pictures!
first, you have me and rbg 💜
then, that's my governor, kate brown (@oregongovbrown) a longtime fulltime pro-choice champion!
two of our congressional delegation that always stand up for human rights and equity... u.s. representatives @repbonamici and @defazio4oregon
naral's ed, @grayson dempsey, nailed it... her words were all our hearts...
next, these two -- @rep.jenniferwilliamson and multnomah county commissioner @jessicavegapederson -- hilariously holding the crowd while waiting for a special apprearance. 
and, u.s. senator merkley (@senjeffmerkley) who read the stories of 30 oregon sexual assault survivors on the senate floor yesterday, voted against kavanaugh, flew across the country and came directly to the gala to as he said " be with family" from the airport.
and a reminder for oregonians to vote no on m106 (@nocuts2care) 😍

yeah, i needed all these people and all the hugs and all the knowing looks yesterday. thank you, thank you, thank you! 
and special thanks to @shaunapdx for including me at your table 👍🏽 i'm getting strong again. onward.

#getpissed #resist #persist

text:
yesterday on #worldmentalhealthday it was inspiring to see so many people talk about mental health, & it reminded me how incredibly grateful i am for the people who stuck by me in college, when i was at my lowest—extremely depressed, with anxiety & ptsd from an abusive relationship. i still don’t know why i deserved that much love. sometimes it’s hard for me now to talk about things i still struggle with, because i don’t want to let those people down.. but i’m working on it. i‘m also working on stepping back from my own issues to show others who are struggling that they deserve all that love too. to anyone reading this—please never hesitate to message me if you ever need someone to talk to♥️
{ sending love to a few of those beautiful people who never let me drown😘 @renee_elizabeth_salai @mikaylaloreen @kendraallen12 @em_joyce24 @emilyboda @kayvelocci @iche2108 }
.
.
.

text:
day 3: today, on the third day of #navratri, we worship yet another manifestation of  ma durga.
#chandraghanta is the avatar that symbolises bravery and beauty.
as the legend has it, lord shiva arrived at raja himavan’s palace in a terrorising form, thereby scaring him and his wife maina devi. it was then that parvati (king himavan’s daughter who shiva had come with the very reason of marrying) had transformed into chandraghanta and convinced him to change into a handsome prince.

chandraghanta, as the name suggests, means ‘the one who has a half moon shaped as a bell.’ the eight hands of the goddess, carry a trishul, gadha, sword, bell, lotus, bow & arrow, kamandal, and one hand risen in a blessing posture.
with a golden complexion, and a half moon on her forehead, the goddess depicts regal beauty and grace. however there is a third eye in the middle of the forehead suggesting that if angered, she has the courage and power to slay the demons coming her way.
it is said that during her battle with the demons, there was a terrible sound produced by the bell that sent them straight to the abode of yama, the god of death. .
.
drawing parallels with modern times, doesn’t this avatar of the goddess remind you of all the brave woman who have raised their voices in the #metoo movement? 
with the blessings of the devi, let us stand by them in their battle against the perpetrators of sexual misconduct. let the demons know that beauty does not only mean vulnerability, that every woman has the power of ma chandraghanta, and if rubbed the wrong way can drive them to hell. 
may our courage reach her moon.
may our voices be her bell. .
.
#navratri2018 #navdurga #madurga #navratricollection #instathoughts #navratriseries #navratrispecial #womanempowerment #woman #goddess #worship #courage
name: Priyanka Naik

text:
look, i get it. asking women out when you are more sensitive than ever to the increasingly apparent harassment women deal with on a daily basic can be anxiety-inducing— esp. when most of the pressure is on the man to make the first move and you‘re a good guy who wouldn’t want to make a woman uncomfortable. but when you have so many hetero men out there prioritizing these feelings over the fact that so many women are hurt by men every day, every minute, all around the world, we have a real problem. we need more men actually doing the *work*— leading change and teaching other men— rather than focusing energy on their discomfort.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#metoo #dating #socialjustice #feminism #feminismformen #men #masculinity #genderroles #sexualassault #violence #writing #thoughts

text:
thank you to jenny gilmore for allowing us to share her informative and hopeful speech from the casv candle lighting ceremony for those who were not able to attend. 
i would like to acknowledge the traditional owners of this and land and pay my respects to their elders, past and present. 
those of us who have been involved in this sector for a long time can often feel despondent about the slow pace of change. but as i reflect on this issue in relation to sexual violence it seems to me that there is real reason to feel some hope that change might be moving in the right direction. 
i’d like to share with you the story of a woman that i suspect many of you will never have heard of. her name is tarana burke and she is a civil rights activist in america and has worked for many years with african american young women who have experienced sexual violence. many years ago now she was supporting a young 13 year old girl who confided in her about her experience of sexual assault. tarana says that she felt speechless at the time and didn’t know how to respond. later when she was reflecting on this she wished that she had simply said to her, me too. 
tarana burke was the founder of the metoo movement back in 2006 however she was unknown until october last year when the well known actress alyssa milano, in response to the allegations of sexual violence spreading over hollywood, sent a tweet asking women to retweet her words with the hashtag metoo if they had too had experienced sexual violence.

it was on the 15 october 2017, around midday, that alyssa milano sent her tweet. by the end of that day the hashtag had been used more than 200,000 time; 24 hours later more than 500,000 times and by early november the #metoo had been tweeted 2.3 million times in 85 different countries. and on  facebook #metoo was used by more than 4.7 million people during the first 24 hours. it became clear very quickly that sexual assault was a massive issue not just in hollywood but in all sectors and walks of life and in all countries. 
both tarana burke and alyssa milano have said clearly that their intention in beginning the #metoo movement was to raise ... see facebook for the full speech

text:
i wanna talk about something that is somewhat controversial. believing all women vs believing evidence. 2 sides to many sexual assault cases. where do i stand? the middle. why? because a person could randomly say "justin bieber assaulted me" in hopes of getting fame. to say i believe all but don't believe them would make me hypocritical. but to believe evidence means i couldn't believe childhood victims like myself. so i listen to the story, every side of the story available. if there's evidence i look at it, if not i rely on the stories and who's sharing the stories. more often than not i believe the victim because it's very rare i come across a story that is blatantly obvious they're lying. what i'm trying to say is, don't believe all women(people) but also don't just believe evidence. be somewhat in the middle, actually read the stories don't just hop on bandwagons. sorry this is so long just something i've wanted to share.

text: i am the most general face of a human being. i aim to do everything in my life to it's best ends. i am exactly what you are, high hopes from life, a 24*7 happy place to live and everything people wish for, except one thing, five months back there was an incident, which increased my anexity my stress levels and what not. and at first just like many probably everyone, i said to myself, " you are overthinking" just stay calm and i neglected it. but a few days later, it was bought to my notice by a friend of mine, he noticed my diet intake and sleep and even weight had drastically reduced. he asked wether everything's fine, i just as everyone says, said, "yes, i am fine, thank you so much for asking" and moved on again a couple of days later my head, and my joints on hand and legs and my waist started paining tremendously. and again i also consider myself over smart, so i decided to find out the reason, but no physical efforts were done for such amount of pain, so i googled, and for the first time in my life, google diagnosed me correctly, and it wasn't cancer, all these effects of mental and physical pain were just due to my mental health. i decided to visit a doctor, so i tried finding out the clinics and i noticed there weren't many, fyi: i live in mumbai. the new one though. and the ones i found were not affordable all by myself, i am graduate student. i knew i needed to talk about this to someone, but unfortunately there was no one i would be comfortable with, so i tried those online sessions where we get a  free session before the payment. so i did just that one session, the doctor there was a bit more supportive, he had extended that one session by an hour or so, since he was keen to know all of my story and help me through it. that was something like three hours. in that three hours he didn't give me a mantra or something, he just showed a few things about myself, and a few things about people. and it did help me a lot. what did he say to me? that something for myself is to be kept to myself. why did i waste your five minutes to tell you nothing and telling you my personal story, first talking is good and i read...( continued in comments below)

text: sneak peak of my latest blog titled: why you can’t “just get over it” this is one of the most unhelpful phrases you can tell someone who has experienced sexual assault. “just get over it”. trauma just isn’t able to go away that easily. it becomes imbedded in the body and the brain. someone who has experienced trauma will be affected the rest of their life in some shape or form. trust me, i tried to stuff it down. i tried very hard to stuff it down and ignore it, but it didn’t work. ——— read more at aboutagirl.net ——— #openingupmystory #metoo #recovery #aboutagirl #youcantjustgetoverit #justtakeitonedayatatime

.

.

text:
geez, what a crazy week ☔️
i honestly don’t know what to say. i’m hurt, as are many others, to witness history unfolding this way. i’m not going to rant, but i #believewomen. almost every single woman i know has been assaulted in some way, including myself. you’re more likely to get struck by lightening than have a false accusation... and believe me, women wouldn’t relive their trauma just for “fame” 😑
.
anyways, it’s also #mentalhealthawareness day, which is important to mention. i’ve had anxiety for a long time, most days are okay, but the past few have been rough between the rain (which i actually love) and personal stress. designing and doodling, like practicing my cursive, help keep my mind at ease, as well as drives around the town and cuddles with my guy. it’s important to have a support system and i’m incredibly thankful for mine ✨
.
and once again, if you read this far, you’re amazing and i’m still grateful for the love and support. this keeps me accountable and sane 😘 #alenaleedesigns

text:
yes, everyday is mental health day around here. depression/adhd/anxiety/eating disorders/addictions/ptsd. either we've got it or know someone who does.
🔸
my family history is riddled with generations of alcoholism, depression, trauma and suicide.
🔸
our family has been blessed to have access to treatment, therapy and healing. many who went before us didn't have the resources or support to get help. 🔸
recovery is hard work but being in the war zone of mental illness and addiction with constant confusion, crisis, heartache and disappointment is even harder.
🔸
keep on keeping on my friends and walking towards the light. you are loved and you are not alone - even though it feels like it. you are actually surrounded by a halo of us all in varying stages of recovery and mental wellness. 🔸
if this post helps someone feel not all alone and gives hope, then it's worth it.
🔸

text:
day 11 of inktober. "cruel"

i was going to draw a reference to the families being torn apart at the us /mexico border. and then i remembered the assault survivors and all the women listening to crap about "the war on men" and the #metoo movement. and then i thought of all the innocents who were murdered for the color of their skin. and trans gender folk who just want to use the bathroom. so many homeless. and people losing their medical aid..and then i think of all baby cows being stolen from their mothers so adults of another species can drink their milk...and so much needless pain so people can trust the "safness" of their cosmetics..the list goes on and on and on....
sensory overload.
emotional overlode. 
it's enough to drive one mad. .
.
.
(not a self portrait however)
.
.
#inktober2018 #inktober #cruel

text:
fellas- i don’t care if the girl is lying wide open on a couch looking like this. unless there is verbal consent, there is no consent. rape is not the result/fault of a female’s appearance. a woman’s body language is not an excuse for illegal (not to mention immoral) behavior. a girl can be licking her own crotch in front of you and that still does not give you permission. “no” means “no,” and consent = a verbal “yes.” 😼

text:
video premiere of #goldenprophet on @rollingstone today (link in bio) in celebration of @unwomen
#dayofthegirl and the power and courage of so many survivors .
i wrote golden prophet about my experience with sexual abuse. it’s the one thing that i can honestly say has
affected every aspect of my life. as with many survivors, it took me a long time to come to grips with it, let alone
share it. it’s been a long road to recovery and writing golden prophet was just another stage in healing. i can only hope by sharing our stories we can continue to help all of the women and girls who have lived through this. our power lies within us. #somospoderosas. - @roxinyofficial .

text:
i was followed tonight. he followed me from inside a store and to my car. i turned around abruptly and glared at him, he moved around like he was walking somewhere else. i went back towards the store and he started following me again! he shouted "excuse me, miss?" a few times before i turned back to face him again. all this mother fucker said was, "you're really, really pretty." what the fuck???? i had my car keys between my fingers and my nails ready to gouge out some eyeballs. i was sweating. i was terrified. i had heard this man shuffling close behind me for almost 10 minutes. i nervously giggled, thanked him, and practically ran back into the store. he decided shouting at me and following me longer was a good idea. he kept trying to get me to stop walking and talk to him. all i could do was walk faster back inside the building to find my husband. i couldn't even open my mouth to tell him to fuck off.
i carry a knife on my person at all times. i have long, sharp acrylic nails for permanent protection. i've been attacked before. i've trusted the wrong person before. get too close and i'll start slashing. 
#ineverfeelsafe #carryprotection

text:
this little girl.
she was so happy.
she was a good girl.
she was responsible at a very young age.
she was praised for helping.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
being a good girl created a belief.

achievement = love
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
you see, this little girl was ignored. 
she begged for attention, but the adults in her life were too busy with their own dysfunction.

she felt all alone. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ but when she was a 'good girl,' she got praise.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
until being a 'good girl' wasn't enough.

she wasn't good enough.

nothing she did seem to bring her the love and attention she craved. 
not even being a noted and celebrated athlete. 
not even getting into a good college on scholarship.
nothing.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
now, i know better. i get to choose my thoughts.

i get to feel more than enough any time i want. 
no one can make me think and feel a certain way.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
only you are in charge of these things.
it's your superpower.
the superpower of choice.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
if you haven't used it, now is the time.

text_retweet:
i had big dreams!
i still do!
but, in 1995 a sick rapist broke into my home while i was sleeping and changed my world. we caught him a month after the attack, prosecuted him, i testified, and he's in jail for life (60 years, 30 years before 1st parole hearing). i ❤ texas, the austin police, and the das that worked my case.
.
a stab wound, rape, death threat, ptsd, major anxiety, sleep disorder, panic attacks, ibs, tmj, immune problems, and a lot of other challenges adjusted my timeline about 20 years. i have been fighting to stay in the game of life for 23 years. getting benched sucks! it's a fight to get back on the first string! i'm trying to be a starter again! i want to make a difference in the world! i am going to add value to the world again and help others! he is not keeping me benched any longer. my fears are not keeping me benched any longer. i don't want any more little girls to get benched!
. 
report rapes! report date rapes! testify! prevent others from being attacked! it's key to your recovery! educate children to be safe. 💗💗💗 #repost @thejhf
• • • • •

text:
i’ve never ever felt like i fit in anywhere. i just wasn’t “like” the other girls in high school or college and damn that hurt so bad. 
_

even as an adult, i felt left out when i didn’t get invited on girl trips and get togethers that “friends” planned. and that pain used to cut deep.

_

but at some point, i decided what i really wanted was to be at peace me! i wanted to embrace my imperfections and love my weirdness - because they are me! 
_

i don’t want to be “like” anyone else. i’m a person who feels stuff (maybe) harder than usual, thinks deeply about too much, and let’s her heart drag her head around at times.  why did i let all of that throw me for such a wild ride of stress, anxiety, and even depression?! _

it’s taken work, and i won’t lie... it’s not always easy.  but now, i #justbreathe and let my weird light shine bright! 
_

i’ve come to appreciate that those things make me me and that’s not bad. it’s actually super special! ⭐️ _

but i know some of you can relate and sometimes feel yourself slipping. (if you’re one of us, you know exactly when i mean)

_

if that’s you, please heed these words: hang on tight and just breathe. i promise whatever you’re feeling, it’s not at an end stop.  remember we have the power to mark that spot with semicolon! know that we’re meant to keep going because we are made for more! ✌🏼❤️ _

#fallfashion #fempreneur #semicolonproject #ptsdawareness #postpartumdepression #shinebright #ceo #mompreneur #metoo
name: 🦋 LORI 🦋

text:
the lottery of the abused. how long should we accept rape and sexual abuse? the metoo campaign has helped a lot to put the focus on this, but it's still a long, long way to go:
the facts remain (here based upon official statistics from norway and the uk). it's only one out of ten of those being raped who actually goes to the police and report this crime. yes, then we are down to ten percent.
out of those who actually report a rape, only about one out of ten reported rapist who gets convicted. do the math: this making rape the crime a criminal person is almost sure not to be convicted of. the question should be: how long will we accept this lottery of the abused?
to put this painting in a historical context, i based the setup upon a painting by the norwegian painter and writer christian krohg who in 1886 wrote the novel albertine. the day after the publication of the novel, the book was confiscated by the police. in 1888 the supreme court of norway upheld the confiscation of the book that told the story of the girl albertine who was raped and from that became a prostitute.
in 1887 krogh finished the painting albertine at the police doctor's waiting room, a painting now at the national gallery in oslo.
but, this is 2018 - and rape is still the 'safest' crime criminals can get away with? is this what we call a civilised society?
in front of the door on this painting, i painted a police, a judge and a politician - the same three on the blackboard on the wall.
the rest are the abused, the victims of rape. it's so many that's needed for one rapist to be convicted. yes, it's so many people that i had to use the ancient technique of painting more persons behind each person.
my question is then: #howlong will it take before these 2 will be #metoo?

.
.

text:
the 2018 theme of international day of the girl is “a skilled girlforce,” which is all about giving young girls the education and support they need to be able to succeed in the workforce — especially because 600 million of them are adolescents who will be of working age very soon.⠀
⠀

text: hoy día de la niña ( no sabía que existía este día hasta hoy ) me gustaría dedicar esta imagen a #natashakampusch quien a los 10 años fue secuestrada y permaneció 8 años bajo el yugo de un hombre, aparentemente normal, un vecino, un señor del barrio, quien jamás tuvo algún acto ilegal en su hoja de vida, pero con la mente demasiado perversa. la historia de esta chica la conocí por la película en #netflix #3096days  luego seguí con su libro autobiográfico y desde ese entonces pienso en el horror que vivió durante 8 años, pero lo que realmente me asombró de la historia es la inmensa confianza que tuvo natasha en ella misma, siempre se tuvo fe, siempre creyó en ella ( claro tuvo sus bajones). tuvo el poder de programar su mente para poder salir adelante. puedo llegar a entender su mente fría, no fue poca cosa lo que vivió... esto ocurrió en viena, lejos de acá pero tan cerca de la vida de tantas niñas en américa, europa, asia, hasta en la casa de al lado, hasta en la habitación de tu propio hogar... hoy natasha se ha convertido en mi heroína, su historia me enseñó que pudo ser peor y que la vida es todo lo que tú quieras que sea y no lo que los demás quieran!!! #metoo #aminiña #díadelaniña👩‍👧 🎈 #fuerte #díainternacionaldelasniñas

text:
a poem from the free ebook “anything but love poems.” see bio for a link to where you can get your free copy. .
anything but love poems

i read love poems
and my jealousy shoots 
fireworks from broken beer bottles.
just a big bang followed by a fizzle.

i cannot write love poems.

my last love tried to kill me.
failed.  and attempted 
two more times to finish me off.
i survived.

i do not write love poems. 
all i have learned of the heart
is that people who truly love you
do not try to kill you.  not once, not twice,
and certainly not three times
in one night.

i do not have a love poem to write.

all i have is that i survived,
that i lived on to write
anything but love poems.
.
.
.

text:
the hardest person to come out to is yourself. i've had to come out twice in my lifetime: as a gay man and as a sexual assault survivor. neither time was fun or easy but necessary to become the person i'm meant to be. thanks to all the people who made space for me to grow! i'm grateful to all of the queer people before me, who made it possible for me to bloom in a safer part of the world.
-
these photos were taken at a gay camp, where men healed each other by sharing stories of trauma, leaning on each other for support, dancing into the night, being silly and open. i declared my years of being tortured by my trauma over and was reborn even stronger and light than before. we had a homecoming-themed prom, where i won homecoming queen. it was the prom i always wanted and needed. it reminded me that no amount of mud i get stuck in, i will always rise and soar with brilliant wings stretched wide, like a bird of paradise.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#nationalcomingoutday #comingout #inspiteof #instagay #faerie #fae #birdofparadise #sexualassault #metoo #assaultsurvivor

trigger warning** yesterday was #worldmentalhealthday and since it has been about a year since #metoo started, i would like to share my story for the first time publicly, albeit the very brief version. my experiences led me to struggle in areas of mental health. i spent years feeling ashamed of that and eating to cope, but no longer. this is exactly why i try to preach “breaking the big mentality.” i know my experience is neither universal or unique, but i hope that by sharing my story i can help someone else find a spark in their worth too. .
.
.

text: i love dark and moody photos. today i’ve been very dark and moody myself. 🤷🏼‍♀️ feeling very introverted and melancholic, if i’m being honest. some days it feels so much easier to convey my thoughts/feelings/mood through a photo or lyrics than through words. i used to think that feeling this way wasn’t acceptable. although it’s changing a bit, mental health has been a taboo topic of conversation. maybe because it makes other people feel uncomfortable? i’m not sure. i’ve kind of learned to not fight it. to sit with my thoughts and feelings and really examine them. so that’s what i’m doing today. sending you all love today. 🌻

text: this is late. and i’ve expressed a lot about my own mental health on here before to the point that i’m sure you’re all aware of it. instead i’d like to take the combination of national mental health awareness day and the #metoo movement. this is me holding a man in my arms lovingly despite him having raped me at least a couple times knowingly. poor mental health makes you vulnerable and afraid of reporting things someone has done wrong to you because they gaslight you. this is a short caption because i still don’t have the ability to put my experience into words even though it’s been over 4 years in my past but i hope other people are stronger and actually seek therapy for such events as i was too afraid. discover red flags and don’t ignore them.

text_retweet:
#repost @sneh_kavi (@get_repost)
・・・
एक स्त्री म्हणून समाजात वावरणं म्हणजे जोखमीचंच काम झालंय. ती समाजात सुरक्षित तर नाहीयेच पण आता तर ती घरातदेखील सुरक्षित नाही राहिली.
रोज बातम्या ऐकतो, कुठं 5 वर्षाच्या बलिकेवर तर कुठं 65 वर्षाच्याही आज्जीवर बलात्कार झालेला किती तरी वेळा कानावर आलंय. पुरुषी वासना एवढी घाणेरडी कशी असते हो ? रोज त्याच वासनेने भरलेल्या नजरा सहन करत आम्ही समाजात वावरतो, का तर आम्हाला आमचं आयुष्य सिद्ध करायचं असत. रस्त्याने चालत असताना जेव्हा एखादा छातीकडे टक लावून बघत असतो तेव्हा किती ओंगळवाण वाटत असेल हे फक्त एक स्त्रीच समजू शकते.
स्त्रीभ्रूणहत्येपासून ते वेगवेगळ्या स्पर्शापर्यंत, flirting पासून ते घाणेरड्या चॅट पर्यंत, घाणेरड्या चॅट पासून शरीरसंबंधाच्या मागण्यांपर्यंत, तिच्याबद्दल खराब बोलण्यापासून ते तिच्याबद्दलच्या खोट्या अफवा पसरवण्यापर्यंत,घाणेरड्या कॉल पासून "हो म्हण नाहीतर ऍसिड टाकू किंवा गायब करू" इथवर,रस्त्यावरच्या घाण कॉमेंट्स पासून ते बसमध्ये खेटून केलेल्या घाणेरड्या स्पर्शापर्यंत, प्रेमसंबंधातल्या लैंगिक अत्याचारापासून ते लग्नानंतरच्या समाजमान्य बलात्कारापर्यंत सगळं सगळं काही स्त्री सहन करते. जागतिक विश्लेषनानुसार 3 स्त्रियांमधली 1 स्त्री याची शिकार आहे. लहानपण अल्लड असतं, तेव्हा झालेले लैगिंक स्पर्श नवीन असतात, त्यांचा परिणाम खोलवर होतो. पुढे तारुण्य अन प्रौढावस्थेतही तेच तेच अनुभव, तेच अत्याचार अन तोच समाज !!!
खूप कमी स्त्रिया व्यक्त होतात. आणि एखादी व्यक्त झाली की मग समाजातले पुरुषच नाही तर स्त्रीयासुद्धा त्यांनाच दोषी ठरवतात, "ती तशीच असेल म्हणून तिच्यासोबत अस झालं" असं म्हणायला पण समाज मागेपुढे पहात नाही. मग तीच तुमच्यासाठी रां*,छि**,कुलटा बनते. पण त्याच जागी स्वतःला नाहीतर आपल्या आयाबहिणीला ठेऊन बघा प्रत्येकाने मग कळेल, पण एक विसरलेच मी, आपल्या समाजात तर आयाबहिणीवर पण अत्याचार झालेल्या बातम्या ऐकल्यात मी ! कसं जगायचं अशा समाजात? आवाज उठवला अत्याचाराविरोधात तरी तोंड दाबलं जातं इथं. गुन्हेगार सुटतो पुन्हा एकदा अत्याचार करण्यासाठी आणि स्त्रीच जगणं अगदी नकोसं होत. मग आठणींचा बोजा अन घुसमटलेला श्वास घेऊन कुठवर जगायचं ????
व्यक्त व्हायचं की अव्यक्त रहायचं ?
-©मिस्नेहा
pic credit:- @aakash.a.dhumal
(#metoo या जागतिक चळवळीच्या निमित्ताने लिहिली गेलीय ही पोस्ट, तसं तर अजून खूप व्यक्त व्हायचंय या विषयावर)

रोज बातम्या ऐकतो, कुठं 5 वर्षाच्या बलिकेवर तर कुठं 65 वर्षाच्याही आज्जीवर बलात्कार झालेला किती तरी वेळा कानावर आलंय. पुरुषी वासना एवढी घाणेरडी कशी असते हो ? रोज त्याच वासनेने भरलेल्या नजरा सहन करत आम्ही समाजात वावरतो, का तर आम्हाला आमचं आयुष्य सिद्ध करायचं असत. रस्त्याने चालत असताना जेव्हा एखादा छातीकडे टक लावून बघत असतो तेव्हा किती ओंगळवाण वाटत असेल हे फक्त एक स्त्रीच समजू शकते.
स्त्रीभ्रूणहत्येपासून ते वेगवेगळ्या स्पर्शापर्यंत, fliing पासून ते घाणेरड्या चॅट पर्यंत, घाणेरड्या चॅट पासून शरीरसंबंधाच्या मागण्यांपर्यंत, तिच्याबद्दल खराब बोलण्यापासून ते तिच्याबद्दलच्या खोट्या अफवा पसरवण्यापर्यंत,घाणेरड्या कॉल पासून "हो म्हण नाहीतर ऍसिड टाकू किंवा गायब करू" इथवर,रस्त्यावरच्या घाण कॉमेंट्स पासून ते बसमध्ये खेटून केलेल्या घाणेरड्या स्पर्शापर्यंत, प्रेमसंबंधातल्या लैंगिक अत्याचारापासून ते लग्नानंतरच्या समाजमान्य बलात्कारापर्यंत सगळं सगळं काही स्त्री सहन करते. जागतिक विश्लेषनानुसार 3 स्त्रियांमधली 1 स्त्री याची शिकार आहे. लहानपण अल्लड असतं, तेव्हा झालेले लैगिंक स्पर्श नवीन असतात, त्यांचा परिणाम खोलवर होतो. पुढे तारुण्य अन प्रौढावस्थेतही तेच तेच अनुभव, तेच अत्याचार अन तोच समाज !!!
खूप कमी स्त्रिया व्यक्त होतात. आणि एखादी व्यक्त झाली की मग समाजातले पुरुषच नाही तर स्त्रीयासुद्धा त्यांनाच दोषी ठरवतात, "ती तशीच असेल म्हणून तिच्यासोबत अस झालं" असं म्हणायला पण समाज मागेपुढे पहात नाही. मग तीच तुमच्यासाठी रां*,छि**,कुलटा बनते. पण त्याच जागी स्वतःला नाहीतर आपल्या आयाबहिणीला ठेऊन बघा प्रत्येकाने मग कळेल, पण एक विसरलेच मी, आपल्या समाजात तर आयाबहिणीवर पण अत्याचार झालेल्या बातम्या ऐकल्यात मी ! कसं जगायचं अशा समाजात? आवाज उठवला अत्याचाराविरोधात तरी तोंड दाबलं जातं इथं. गुन्हेगार सुटतो पुन्हा एकदा अत्याचार करण्यासाठी आणि स्त्रीच जगणं अगदी नकोसं होत. मग आठणींचा बोजा अन घुसमटलेला श्वास घेऊन कुठवर जगायचं ????
व्यक्त व्हायचं की अव्यक्त रहायचं ?

stop_filter_tweet: ( et_repost ) ・・・ एक स्त्री म्हणून समाजात वावरणं म्हणजे जोखमीचंच काम झालंय . ती समाजात सुरक्षित तर नाहीयेच पण आता तर ती घरातदेखील सुरक्षित नाही राहिली . रोज बातम्या ऐकतो , कुठं 5 वर्षाच्या बलिकेवर तर कुठं 65 वर्षाच्याही आज्जीवर बलात्कार झालेला किती तरी वेळा कानावर आलंय . पुरुषी वासना एवढी घाणेरडी कशी असते हो ? रोज त्याच वासनेने भरलेल्या नजरा सहन करत आम्ही समाजात वावरतो , का तर आम्हाला आमचं आयुष्य सिद्ध करायचं असत . रस्त्याने चालत असताना जेव्हा एखादा छातीकडे टक लावून बघत असतो तेव्हा किती ओंगळवाण वाटत असेल हे फक्त एक स्त्रीच समजू शकते . स्त्रीभ्रूणहत्येपासून ते वेगवेगळ्या स्पर्शापर्यंत , fliing पासून ते घाणेरड्या चॅट पर्यंत , घाणेरड्या चॅट पासून शरीरसंबंधाच्या मागण्यांपर्यंत , तिच्याबद्दल खराब बोलण्यापासून ते तिच्याबद्दलच्या खोट्या अफवा पसरवण्यापर्यंत , घाणेरड्या कॉल पासून `` हो म्हण नाहीतर ऍसिड टाकू किंवा गायब करू '' इथवर , रस्त्यावरच्या घाण कॉमेंट्स पासून ते बसमध्ये खेटून केलेल्या घाणेरड्या स्पर्शापर्यंत , प्रेमसंबंधातल्या लैंगिक अत्याचारापासून ते लग्नानंतरच्या समाजमान्य बलात्कारापर्यंत सगळं सगळं काही स्त्री सहन करते . जागतिक विश्लेषनानुसार 3 स्त्रियांमधली 1 स्त्री याची शिकार आहे . लहानपण अल्लड असतं , तेव्हा झालेले लैगिंक स्पर्श नवीन असतात , त्यांचा परिणाम खोलवर होतो . पुढे तारुण्य अन प्रौढावस्थेतही तेच तेच अनुभव , तेच अत्याचार अन तोच समाज ! ! ! खूप कमी स्त्रिया व्यक्त होतात . आणि एखादी व्यक्त झाली की मग समाजातले पुरुषच नाही तर स्त्रीयासुद्धा त्यांनाच दोषी ठरवतात , `` ती तशीच असेल म्हणून तिच्यासोबत अस झालं '' असं म्हणायला पण समाज मागेपुढे पहात नाही . मग तीच तुमच्यासाठी रां* , छि** , कुलटा बनते . पण त्याच जागी स्वतःला नाहीतर आपल्या आयाबहिणीला ठेऊन बघा प्रत्येकाने मग कळेल , पण एक विसरलेच मी , आपल्या समाजात तर आयाबहिणीवर पण अत्याचार झालेल्या बातम्या ऐकल्यात मी ! कसं जगायचं अशा समाजात ? आवाज उठवला अत्याचाराविरोधात तरी तोंड दाबलं जातं इथं . गुन्हेगार सुटतो पुन्हा एकदा अत्याचार करण्यासाठी आणि स्त्रीच जगणं अगदी नकोसं होत . मग आठणींचा बोजा अन घुसमटलेला श्वास घेऊन कुठवर जगायचं ? ? ? ? व्यक्त व्हायचं की अव्यक्त रहायचं ? आवाज उठवला अत्याचाराविरोधात तरी तोंड दाबलं जातं इथं . गुन्हेगार सुटतो पुन्हा एकदा अत्याचार करण्यासाठी आणि स्त्रीच जगणं अगदी नकोसं होत . मग आठणींचा बोजा अन घुसमटलेला श्वास घेऊन कुठवर जगायचं ? ? ? ? व्यक्त व्हायचं की अव्यक्त रहायचं ? text:
“i’m a very average woman that’s very noisy. i invite you to be noisy with me. pick up the baton, this world needs you.” -jessica lenahan, at an emotional standing ovation for the film home truth at the university of miami. .
.
#hometruth is about domestic violence survivor and human rights advocate jessica lenahan, who, after her three daughters are abducted and killed in violation of a restraining order, embarks upon a journey to create change. .
.
jessica’s lawyer carrie bettinger lopez, directs the university of miami legal clinic @umlawhrc and she served as the white house advisor on violence against women during president obama’s administration. .
.
our amazing colleague, erin sorenson, founder of @3rdstage was the champion impact producer of home truth. .
.
watch the film at hometruthfilm.com 👀
.
.
thank you @womensfundmiami for this!
#film #documentaryfilmmaking #documentaryfilm #impactproduction #miami #justice #voice #speakup #speakupspeakout #metoo

text:
to all the boys and men who helped me heal… thank you.
🙏🏻
to my blood brothers, whose friendship gave me the reason to keep reaching through it all because i had proof of a worthy place to aim for... thank you.
🙏🏻
and to all the brothers who became that proof, gracing me with a space in which i could just be—not woman or conquest, not victim or survivor—just me... thank you.
🙏🏻
to the boy who took me in that night, who didn’t have the words but whose presence was all i needed... thank you.
🙏🏻
to the doctor who didn’t hide his empathy behind his white coat, whose eyes told me i was safe and who eased me through the examination as if i were his most cherished daughter... thank you.
🙏🏻
and to all the fathers who loved me like a daughter, who let me walk like a woman and still break like a little girl... thank you.
🙏🏻
to my grandfather who believed me and loved me in spite of the antiquated judgments of his peers... thank you.
🙏🏻
to my high school sweetheart who inked “no matter what” on my hand as we awaited my hiv verdict... thank you.
🙏🏻
and to that same sweetheart who let me be a virgin again so that i could have that first time i deserved... thank you.
🙏🏻
to all the lovers who paused for my tears to patiently hold my trauma, who loved me through my shame and to the other side... thank you.
🙏🏻
to the man i married, my ‘toro’, who encouraged my fire to roar like never before, to raise my voice and my power without apology... thank you.
🙏🏻
and to all the men who got angry for me when i couldn’t, who are angry for us now, who want to hold us, protect us, and lift us up... thank you.
🙏🏻
you each gave me, and continue to give us, a worthy place to aim for—a riverbed for our tears, a guardian for our fears—and now, as we women rise, know that i pray we rise together. let us not merely displace the shame onto men and the power onto women. it is our common inheritance; and it is in the balance of masculine and feminine, together, where, as the toltec say, “we become as god”.
💘 rebecca
.
#heforshe #embracedmasculine #shamelessfeminine #metoo #whyididntreport #traumhealing #womensreality #yesallwomen #everdaysexism #shero #shamansister

text:
with hashtags like #metoo and #timesup trending right now, the theme for @objectifscentre’s #womeninphotography exhibition this year, collective power, is both apt and timely.
.
.
the exhibition showcases six women photographers who seek to empower and effect change within and across communities through their work..
.
whether it is the tragic plight of rohingya women (@w0ngmayee) or the insecurities and self-doubts that afflict a young woman in modern japanese society (@miyazakiizumi) you will not be able to help but empathise with the subjects in this stunning series of images.
.
it’s a fascinating, powerful and deeply moving show, dealing with stories that are both intimate and deeply personal, yet somehow universally true.

text:
true story. my story through poetry.

#nofilter abuse was something she knew very well, the pain she felt the cards she was dealt was beyond hell, no one took the time to really know what she experienced, a maze of oblivion they remained, sorrows deeper than the grave, ooh the physical pain she ached, something like annie are you okay, put a lighter to her face, maybe stab her with a pocketknife, maybe close fist mush her in the face, or how about when she was too young, too young to say no to molestation to say no to rape, the physical pain, pain that meshed with the emotional, mental, and spiritual aspects, she knew what demons were before she was adept, adept to a world that was cold, cold and gullible, maybe she was the gullible one you know the impressionable vulnerable child or how about the impressionable, vulnerable teenager, maybe cutting herself would numb the pain yeah, maybe drugging herself would ease the wounds, maybe, maybe someone would come save her, maybe the light would soon swoon, but she smoked and she smoked some more, she drank, and she was talked about and ignored, she did prescription drugs like oxycodone, and hydrocodone, mixing them with weed and drinks, so slowly she would fall asleep forever, maybe in her own blood if she let her wrists slit, but for the first time it hurt a bit, she knew she could not commit the suicide, because the spirit of life in her had coincided with her being forfeiting the evil that wanted to take her over, entering the new scope of life, with a tumultuous, and long fight, she saw the light, the light was within her, so she shared it even though everything she had was taken, she shared kindness because she numerous times felt her heart breaking, she was an angel with battlewounds, you never know what one goes through, maybe they are just not normal like you 🙇🏾‍♀️🖤
name: 🦄 🔮Avishai El 🌙🔮خالد 🇲🇦

text:
rationing money, stealing money, making them give up all their  money with no access is financial abuse. many millionaires wives live  this life because they live in a beautiful home and have what is deemed  the picture perfect look. but they have no access to funds and have to  almost beg for money. money is crucial in relationships, it shows how  your mate is with money. rather frivolous or spendthrift, you can gauge a  person by how they spend money. being selfish with money and rationing  it out very abusive. many times victims can't get what they need or they  are humiliated before the money is given. working and not seeing your  money is not fair and it's robbery. have you ever been financially  abused? .

text:
october is domestic violence awareness month.  unlike halloween, though, domestic violence is not limited to october, nor should we be aware only these 31 days. domestic violence is a wraith that stalks its prey all year long. abuse victims can be haunted even after the relationship ends: they are more likely to suffer depression and anxiety than are others, less able to form long-term loving relationships, and more likely to engage in harmful, high-risk behaviors, according to the centers for disease control and prevention.
if you know someone in an abusive relationship, please download our flyer & send it to them. if you are into planning & lists, we have made available an "inventory for safety planning." 💜💜💜💜 _______[link in bio]_______
__________________________

text:
today, on the #internationaldayofthegirl, i think of the millions of girls + women who live through so much pain + trauma. whose lives are marked by abuse + fear; who don’t even know there is another way to be in the world.
.
it also makes me consider the way so many of us don’t even realize we’re only half alive—until we get a taste of freedom.
.
may we live lives that are marked by the freedom we ourselves run toward + the generous spirit that jesus gives us as he calls us to love our neighbor as ourselves. #courage

text:
as a woman, i am often perceived as “opinionated” when i am knowledgeable. i am considered unintelligent when i am quiet. i am considered dramatic if advocating for myself or my business.
the men in my life are considered brilliant when they speak about what they know. observant and intelligent when they are quiet. a good negotiator when advocating for themselves or their business.
my empathy and intuition is an upper hand that often must be combated with dismissiveness and condescension. .
i am just speaking about my own experiences. and not all the times i’ve been physically and verbally assaulted. not the many times i’ve been called a bitch because i didn’t want to give him my phone number.
no, i’m talking about the “respectable” men that i deal with all the time.  men i like. .
not all men!! let me make that super clear... i have plenty of experience all the time with men that treat me with respect as an equal being. .
but my point is, it’s insidious.  they don’t even realize they perceive and treat you differently because your female. they perceive themselves as respectful of women... because they open car doors and hire women at their companies. but it’s so deep... a prejudice that has existed for thousands of years... and i for one feel like i am just waking up... the world is actually starting to feel a little bit different to me. .
thanks to these women that are posting pictures of their naked bodies and proclaiming their right to freedom and safety. thanks to the women who are removing the shame around coming forward.
thank you! .
i don’t mean to jump on the bandwagon but i’ve been feeling this in my gut and it’s bubbling up today. we are all inherently good beings that suffer from brainwashing to various degrees. i love men just as i love women and have equal compassion for all. .
everyone has an opinion... an experience to color their paradigm.  but there is, in fact, a single truth beneath all those opinions.
.
.
#weareallone
#womensupportingwomen 
#metoo 
#thankyou 
#goddesses 
#timesup 
#itstime ❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️

text:
rereleasing tonight "3 assault charges" "the first one i filed was against a boy in high school who snuck up behind me and grabbed my breast on the bus. i was a sophomore. as i was exiting i told the bus driver what had happened and she just shrugged her shoulders at me. i didn't understand her response. "am i overreacting?" i thought to myself.
the more i thought about it, the more upset i got. so, i told my mom when i got home that day. she said "oh, don't worry about it. he's young and just wanted to cop a feel." i was floored by her response. didn't she understand that i had been violated and embarrassed? didn't she know that i was stressing that this might become a game for the other boys on the bus if i didn't do anything about it? to me, it wasn't as easy as just chalking it up to "boys being boys" and wait, we didn't live in that era anymore, right? at least, i didn't think we did...
i saw the boy on the bus the next day, he was laughing about it with all of his friends..." read the rest at tirednotdead.com
.
.
#metoo #sexualassault #beingawoman #girls #womenempowerment  #instawomen #speakout #forthegirls #timesup #tirednotdead

text: something’s been on my mind lately. especially in the wake of the kavanaugh confirmation and all of the drama surrounding it. something that has really made me angry is the hashtag #metoo being misconstrued. i’ve seen it posted with the ‘me’ crossed out and ‘him’ in place of it. it was created as a thread to link survivors, regardless of gender, together to say “me too” to echo their own experience with sexual assault. putting ‘him’ in place of ‘me’ in the phrase does two things: 1) insinuates that #metoo is exclusive for women and 2) puts men over women by saying the male specific term ‘him’ instead of the gender neutral term‘me’. #1- is false. the hashtag is gender neutral. #2- is incorrect. feminism is not men>women. in fact, @beyonce defines it quite clearly when she says that it is “the social, political and economic equality of the sexes”. this may sounds like semantics, but seeing it changed and mocked to go against its purpose is unfair. please educate yourself before posting. please have these and other discussions with an open mind. please listen to understand, not to respond. and please, register to vote and get to the polls on november 6. “no one is truly free while anyone is oppressed.” keep on, keeping on. ✊🏿✊🏻✊🏼✊🏽✊🏾
name: Lydia Dorn

text:
in spirit of international #dayofthegirl here’s a shout out to all my girls 👊🏼👯‍♀️👯‍♀️💕
.
there is so much power⚡️ in uniting as girls/women and having a circle of girl friends who you know you can count on and trust to be there for you. .
my best moments have been more exciting and meaningful when i have had the privilege to pop a bottle (or two) with my girl friends!🥂🍾
.
and through my toughest times, my girls have been there to be a shoulder to cry on, eat ice cream and watch some good ol’ netflix.🍦🍷🍫
.
we are 1000% stronger together👊🏼✨so let’s celebrate the potential we have by supporting and empowering each other and remembering to bring other girls up with us as we grow.🙌🏼💛
.
give your girl friends some love by tagging them below 💕
.
📸 main pic taken from one of my jewelry brand’s fun photoshoots @cumbiaofficial ✨
