text:
dear old me,

it is time for you to make the decision to change and to stop thinking that you're way is the only way.
__
it is time for you to begin to work through things from your past and learn how to accept yourself. i want you to know how beautiful you are within. your nose is adorable and doesn't need any changing. your lips are not “too big,” they are wonderfully sweet. nothing is wrong with your hair. please, stop worrying about your weight and appreciate your body and it’s perfect imperfections. you are healthy and able-bodied. enjoy it! look in the mirror and tell yourself how much you are loved. remind yourself that you deserve this love. do it now. if you don’t believe it, try harder until you do. most importantly, stop listening to anyone or anything around you who tells you that you are not good enough. that is a lie. you are smart and talented and have so much to give to the world. 
__

i know it may seem difficult now, but everything happens for a reason. just keep following your path and things will work out as long as you believe in yourself. just be confident. you'll see. that heart that was once broken will mend and lead you exactly where you need to go. so be kind to yourself and learn how to understand your heart. because sometimes you feel like you’re in the wrong place, or maybe even on the wrong planet, but you are blessed to be alive, so live this life to it’s fullest and choose joy. you deserve it. 
love

the future you 🕊

text:
yesterday was mental health awareness day.
yesterday i said goodbye to the best therapist i have worked with.
he gave me a diagnosis i had waited most of my life for. we worked through a course together for two years on coping with complex post traumatic stress disorders with disassociation. i have come so far in my recovery and feel extremely grateful for the support of the mental health services. i'm working closer to being discharged, i have some way to go yet but i'm proud of myself and other service users i met. 
let's keep the mental health conversations happening every day. awareness and education is everything. 
thinking of every one who is experiencing their own fight.
.
illustration by me.
#mentalhealthday #brainday #mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness #mentalhealth #myrecovery #awareness #brainday #spoonie #spoonielife #chronicinsta #chronicillness #ptsd #cptsd #abusesurvivor #metoo

text:
video premiere of #goldenprophet on @rollingstone today (link in bio) in celebration of @unwomen #dayofthegirl and the power and courage of so many survivors like myself.

golden prophet is a short interdisciplinary music video and performance piece featuring a diverse group of women with individual messages for others who have been sexually abused or discriminated against. the handwritten messages in various languages on the dancers’ bodies are meant to ignite the emotional resilience and power we all possess to heal and move forward creating change through movement, sound, and visual storytelling.

directed by @roxinyofficial + @rebeca__diaz

director of photography:  @rebeca__diaz

visual art projections + set design: @michnaofficial + @rebeca__diaz 
edited by: @roxinyofficial + @rubblekings

colorists: @freefolkstudios / @dfrnz

choreography by: @a1exzandra

styling and production assistant: @sarajlundgren

performed by: @roxinyofficial 
featuring:  @a1exzandra, @soraiascicchitano, @jendaya_dash, @cheyenne freeman_, anna brown, @curlysamrulez, @mattcalenders_sister @shears_genius, @agusmignone_ , @amandataysw, @scubamcbrian, @theadairpowers, @blackramonaflowers, @hanakozuka, @maria_bklyn, @julia_gratol,  @mbski77

⭐️
let’s lead our future to a world that is amazing for girls all over. #metoo #metoomovement

text:
back in june 2013, a funk-inspired track dominated the airwaves. inarguably “the song of the summer,” “blurred lines” made a superstar out of robin thicke, provided a good comeback vehicle for t.i., and gave pharrell williams a 45th thing to do that year. ⁣
⁣
presently, the song is wrought with problems. robin thicke made some poor choices that cost him his marriage and his superstar status flamed out like a supernova. a jury ruled that more than $7 million was owed to the family of marvin gaye, whose “got to give it up” straddles the line between “inspiration” and “copyright infringement.” ⁣
⁣
and then there are the lyrics, which essentially offer a 4+ minute thesis on why “no means yes.” sexually aggressive lyrics are a cornerstone of popular music, but the timing of the song’s release and the utter lack of subtlety makes this a hard one to listen to, even just five years later. thicke has argued that he was being cheeky—and i believe he may even believe that—but in the #metoo era, lyrics like “you know you want it” fall flat. it can’t be a coincidence that snl picked it as the soundtrack to last weekend’s gop celebration of kavanaugh's unfathomable confirmation. ⁣
⁣
but let’s cheerfully revisit the time when this undeniably catchy song was tearing up the charts and enlivening pride parades everywhere. thicke’s vocals, gliding effortlessly from chest voice to falsetto, are a (much) better version of timberlake. t.i.’s rap interlude provides a gritty balance. and pharell’s sporadic “everybody get up!” refrain will stand the test of time. ⁣
⁣
others have pointed out the frenzied nature of this song, which in addition to three lead voices, has the equivalent of 4 verses, 4 choruses, and 2 bridges. but the #bestpart—in addition to pharell mugging with a goat (?) in the video—is at the beginning of the third chorus around 2:12, as backing vocals breathe new life into the repeating hook. “i hate them lines … i hate them lines.” it’s a subtle undercurrent, but a nice detail that sets the penultimate chorus apart before t.i.’s rap begins. ⁣
⁣
#robinthicke #pharrellwilliams #ti #blurredlines #marvingaye #popmusic #funkmusic #soulmusic #copyrightinfringement ⁣
